sentences.english: Water the plants but not too heavily.
sentences.chinese: 给幼苗浇些水，但不要太多。

sentences.english: The farmers tamped down the earth around the base of the seedings .
sentences.chinese: 农民们把幼苗基部四周的泥土压实。

sentences.english: FROST】Frost has killed several of our young plants.
sentences.chinese: 霜已搞坏了我们好几株幼苗。

sentences.english: He transplanted the seedlings into peaty soil.
sentences.chinese: 他把幼苗移栽到含泥炭的土壤里。

sentences.english: The responses of tomato seedling to water stress using tensiometer were studied.
sentences.chinese: 水分胁迫对番茄幼苗的生长有严重的抑制作用。

sentences.english: The total cost of the seed lings seedlings and fertilizer is $200. dollars.
sentences.chinese: 包括幼苗和肥料在内所有的花费大约200美元。

sentences.english: Take out as much soil as you can with the seedlings.
sentences.chinese: 尽量让幼苗多带一些土壤。

sentences.english: The enzyme has been partially purified from muny bean shoots.
sentences.chinese: 从绿豆幼苗中已部分地提纯了这种酶。

sentences.english: Children such as seedlings, must develop properly, can only germinate grow.
sentences.chinese: 幼儿比如幼苗，必须培养得宜，方能发芽滋长。

sentences.english: Named cultivars are grafted onto seedling dogwoods.
sentences.chinese: 指定的品种嫁接到山茱萸的幼苗上。

sentences.english: Incomplete leaf length(ILL) is the unique character of seedling trait in rice.
sentences.chinese: 不完全叶器官是水稻所特有的幼苗性状。

sentences.english: The young plants need some coverlets in winter.
sentences.chinese: 这些幼苗在冬天需要覆盖物。

sentences.english: The research was to study the antidotal effect of Zn on pea seedling under Hg stress.
sentences.chinese: 研究锌对汞胁迫下豌豆幼苗的解毒效应。

sentences.english: Plants suffer high mortality in the seedling stage of life history.
sentences.chinese: 幼苗阶段是植物种群生活史中亏损最严重的时期之一。

sentences.english: The content of wheat-esterase in young sprout period is the highest.
sentences.chinese: 以幼苗期的内乡188小麦植物酯酶含量最高。
